---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Credits and licensing"
  description="How Argument Detective is licensed, what it was inspired by, and how it stays independent and noncommercial."
  path="/credits/"
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Fallacies', href: '/' }, { label: 'Credits' }]} />

  <article class="page prose">
    <h1>Credits &amp; licensing</h1>

    <p>
      {site.name} is an independent, noncommercial educational project. Its original classroom explanations,
      examples, activities, and organization were created for gifted students in grades 5–6. The project
      was inspired in part by <em>Your Logical Fallacy Is</em>, created by Jesse Richardson, Andy
      Smith, Som Meaden, and Flip Creative for The School of Thought. Website content from that
      project is published under
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >CC BY-NC 3.0</a
      >. Where any wording has been adapted, the relevant page identifies the source and describes
      the changes. No endorsement is implied. LogicalFallacies.org was consulted as a reference and
      is linked for further reading; its protected content, examples, graphics, and tool designs
      were not reproduced.
    </p>

    <h2>Licenses</h2>
    <ul class="qlist">
      <li>
        <strong>Source code:</strong>
        <a href="https://opensource.org/license/mit" rel="noopener noreferrer">MIT License</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Original educational text and printable resources:</strong>
        <a href={site.contentLicenseUrl} rel="noopener noreferrer">{site.contentLicense}</a>
        (Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Adapted portions:</strong> keep the source-specific notice required by the original license,
        shown on the relevant page.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Third-party packages:</strong> preserve their original licenses, listed in the repository’s
        <code>THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md</code>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Independence</h2>
    <p>
      This site is free to visitors and carries no advertising, sponsorship, affiliate links, or
      paid tier. All 15 topic pages use original explanations and examples written from a blank
      page. Icons are original SVGs created for the project; no reference site’s icon system, page
      layout, or writing was copied.
    </p>

    <h2>References consulted</h2>
    <ul class="qlist">
      <li>
        <a href="https://iep.utm.edu/fallacy/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy: Fallacies</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/fallacies/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy: Fallacies</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a
          href="https://owl.purdue.edu/owl/general_writing/academic_writing/logic_in_argumentative_writing/fallacies.html"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Purdue OWL: Logical Fallacies</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://writingcenter.unc.edu/tips-and-tools/fallacies/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >UNC Writing Center: Fallacies</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://yourlogicalfallacyis.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Your Logical Fallacy Is</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.logicalfallacies.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >LogicalFallacies.org</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
